3. TECHNOLOGY OVERVIEW

3.1 Quantum Computing Foundation

3.1.1 Quantum Advantage in Healthcare

Quantum computing provides exponential speedup for three classes of problems critical to healthcare:

1. Optimization: Patient scheduling, resource allocation, treatment planning
2. Simulation: Molecular interactions, protein folding, epidemiological modeling
3. Machine Learning: Pattern recognition in complex datasets, differential diagnosis

AURA implements a 128-qubit superconducting processor with error correction, providing quantum advantage for real-time clinical decision support.

3.1.2 Quantum-Classical Hybrid Architecture

The system employs a heterogeneous architecture where:

· Classical processors handle sensor fusion, control loops, and user interface
· Quantum processors optimize high-dimensional decisions and simulations
· Quantum-inspired algorithms run on classical hardware where appropriate

This hybrid approach maximizes practical utility while quantum hardware continues to scale.

3.2 6G Communication System

3.2.1 Terahertz Connectivity

AURA utilizes the terahertz spectrum (140-220 GHz) for:

· Ultra-high bandwidth: 100 Gbps for real-time multi-modal data transfer
· Ultra-low latency: 1ms round-trip for haptic teleoperation
· Massive connectivity: Simultaneous links to multiple networks and robots

3.2.2 Network Slicing for Healthcare

Dedicated virtual networks ensure quality of service:

· Slice 1 (URLLC): Remote surgery, emergency control (99.9999% reliability)
· Slice 2 (eMBB): Medical imaging, video consultation (1 Gbps guaranteed)
· Slice 3 (mMTC): Sensor telemetry, routine monitoring (massive device support)

3.2.3 Haptic Communication

Implementation of IEEE 1918.1 (Tactile Internet) standard enables:

· Remote physical examination with force feedback
· Surgical assistance with sub-millimeter precision
· Physical therapy guidance with real-time correction

3.3 Sensor and Perception System

3.3.1 Multi-Modal Sensing

AURA integrates complementary sensing modalities:

Visual:

· 20MP stereo cameras with 140dB dynamic range
· Thermal imaging for inflammation and fever detection
· Hyperspectral imaging for tissue oxygenation assessment
· Polarimetric imaging for surface texture analysis

Biometric:

· Non-invasive glucose monitoring via NIR spectroscopy
· Continuous blood pressure via pulse wave velocity
· 12-lead equivalent ECG via capacitive coupling
· Respiration monitoring via millimeter-wave radar

Environmental:

· Air quality sensors for pathogen detection
· Radiation monitoring for safety in disaster zones
· Structural integrity assessment via LIDAR and acoustics

3.3.2 Sensor Fusion Architecture

A three-tier architecture processes sensor data:

1. Reflex tier: Subconscious processing for safety-critical responses (1ms)
2. Perceptual tier: Conscious processing for environmental understanding (10-100ms)
3. Cognitive tier: Reasoning and planning with quantum optimization (100-1000ms)

3.4 Actuation and Mobility

3.4.1 Biomimetic Design

AURA's 56 degrees of freedom provide human-like movement:

· Series Elastic Actuators for compliant, safe interaction
· Magnetic gearboxes for backdrivability and silent operation
· Distributed processing for coordinated whole-body control

3.4.2 Mobility Performance

· Bipedal walking: 0-5 km/h, handles 30° slopes, 25cm stairs
· Payload capacity: 50kg at full extension, 150kg close to body
· Fall recovery: Can stand from prone position autonomously
· Environmental adaptation: Waterproof to 1.5m, operates -20°C to 60°C

3.5 Artificial Intelligence System

3.5.1 Embodied Intelligence

Unlike disembodied AI, AURA learns through physical interaction:

· Sensorimotor grounding: Concepts tied to physical experiences
· Continuous learning: Improves without forgetting previous knowledge
· Cross-modal transfer: Skills learned in one domain applied to others

3.5.2 Medical AI Architecture

Three-layer knowledge system:

1. Foundation model: Trained on 50 million clinical notes and medical literature
2. Domain adaptation: Fine-tuned for specific medical specialties
3. Personalization: Adapts to individual patients and caregivers

3.5.3 Explainable AI

All decisions are accompanied by:

· Confidence intervals and uncertainty quantification
· Alternative options with relative probabilities
· Evidence citations from medical literature
· Natural language explanations tailored to audience

