5. APPLICATIONS AND USE CASES

5.1 Clinical Healthcare

5.1.1 Hospital Settings

Operating Room Assistant:

· Sterile instrument handling and passing
· Real-time surgical guidance from preoperative imaging
· Vital sign monitoring and alerting
· Documentation automation

Intensive Care Unit:

· Continuous vital sign monitoring (heart rate, respiration, SpO2, etc.)
· Early warning of patient deterioration
· Routine care (turning, oral care, etc.)
· Family communication and updates

General Ward:

· Medication administration with verification
· Patient mobilization and walking assistance
· Basic procedure assistance (wound care, IV monitoring)
· Patient education and discharge instructions

5.1.2 Diagnostic Support

Medical Imaging:

· Patient positioning for scans
· Preliminary image analysis and triage
· Correlation with electronic health records
· Communication of results to patients

Laboratory Assistance:

· Blood draw with vein finding
· Sample handling and transport
· Point-of-care testing operation
· Result interpretation in clinical context

5.2 Elderly and Home Care

5.2.1 Activities of Daily Living

Mobility Assistance:

· Walking support with adaptive assistance level
· Transfer assistance (bed to chair, chair to toilet)
· Fall prevention through gait analysis and support
· Fall detection and emergency response

Personal Care:

· Medication management with dispensing and reminders
· Meal preparation with nutritional optimization
· Hygiene assistance with dignity preservation
· Dressing assistance with garment recognition

5.2.2 Cognitive and Emotional Support

Memory Assistance:

· Reminders for appointments and tasks
· Memory reinforcement through conversation
· Wayfinding assistance in familiar environments
· Connection to family through video calls

Companionship:

· Conversation on topics of interest
· Entertainment (music, games, stories)
· Exercise encouragement and guidance
· Mood monitoring and intervention

5.2.3 Health Monitoring

Continuous Assessment:

· Vital signs without intrusive measurement
· Sleep quality and pattern analysis
· Nutrition and hydration tracking
· Medication adherence monitoring

Early Intervention:

· Detection of health deterioration
· Alert to caregivers or healthcare providers
· Guidance through self-care measures
· Emergency response initiation

5.3 Emergency and Disaster Response

5.3.1 Search and Rescue

Victim Location:

· Through-wall life sign detection (up to 15m)
· Thermal imaging in smoke and darkness
· Audio detection of calls for help
· Structural analysis for safe access

Extraction and Stabilization:

· Debris removal with precision tools
· Victim packaging for safe transport
· Basic life support (airway, breathing, circulation)
· Communication with incident command

5.3.2 Field Medicine

Triage:

· Rapid assessment using START or SALT protocols
· Categorization (immediate, delayed, minimal, expectant)
· Prioritization for treatment and evacuation
· Tracking of multiple victims

Treatment:

· Hemorrhage control (tourniquets, pressure dressings)
· Airway management (positioning, adjuncts)
· Breathing support (oxygen, needle decompression)
· Splinting and spinal immobilization

5.3.3 Hazardous Environment Operations

Chemical, Biological, Radiological, Nuclear (CBRN):

· Detection and identification of hazards
· Operation in contaminated zones without risk to humans
· Decontamination assistance
· Sample collection for analysis

Structural Collapse:

· Navigation through unstable rubble
· Structural integrity assessment
· Shoring and stabilization
· Communication relay deployment

5.4 Specialized Healthcare Applications

5.4.1 Rehabilitation

Physical Therapy:

· Exercise demonstration and guidance
· Assistance and resistance as needed
· Progress tracking with objective metrics
· Motivation through gamification

Neurological Rehabilitation:

· Cognitive exercises for stroke recovery
· Gait training for neurological conditions
· Mirror therapy for phantom limb pain
· Biofeedback for motor control

5.4.2 Mental Health

Therapeutic Interaction:

· Cognitive behavioral therapy exercises
· Mindfulness and meditation guidance
· Social skills training for autism spectrum
· Monitoring of mood and medication effects

Crisis Intervention:

· Suicide risk assessment through conversation analysis
· De-escalation techniques for agitation
· Connection to human crisis resources
· Monitoring for safety

5.4.3 Pediatric Care

Child-Friendly Interaction:

· Age-appropriate communication
· Distraction during procedures
· Education about health conditions
· Play-based therapy and development assessment

Family Support:

· Respite care for parents of chronically ill children
· Sibling interaction and support
· Coordination of complex care schedules
· Education about home care procedures

