7. DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP AND MILESTONES

7.1 Phase 1: Research and Development (2024-2025)

2024: Foundation

· Q1: Quantum processor architecture finalization
· Q2: 6G transceiver prototype development
· Q3: Mechanical design concepts and simulation
· Q4: Software architecture definition and team assembly

Key Milestones:

· Quantum simulation of medical decision algorithms
· 6G link demonstration with haptic feedback
· Mechanical prototype of hand with 20 degrees of freedom
· AI architecture for medical knowledge representation

2025: Component Integration

· Q1: First integrated electronics prototype
· Q2: Quantum processor cryogenic integration
· Q3: Sensor fusion algorithm development
· Q4: First walking prototype

Key Milestones:

· Quantum computation on integrated hardware
· 6G communication at full specification
· Multi-modal sensor fusion demonstration
· Stable bipedal walking on flat terrain

7.2 Phase 2: Alpha and Beta Testing (2026-2027)

2026: Alpha Systems

· Q1: First full hardware prototype
· Q2: Basic software integration
· Q3: Laboratory testing of medical capabilities
· Q4: Alpha deployment to partner facilities

Key Milestones:

· First medical diagnosis assisted by AURA
· Successful navigation in hospital environment
· Demonstration of caregiver assistance tasks
· Initial clinical safety assessment

2027: Beta Testing

· Q1: Beta units to 10 partner hospitals
· Q2: Clinical trials phase 1 (safety)
· Q3: Home care pilot programs
· Q4: Emergency response simulations

Key Milestones:

· Safety certification from regulatory bodies
· Demonstrated ROI in hospital setting
· Positive user feedback from patients and staff
· Successful search and rescue in simulated disaster

7.3 Phase 3: Regulatory Approval and Initial Production (2028)

2028: Market Readiness

· Q1: Regulatory submissions (FDA, CE Mark, etc.)
· Q2: Production line setup and validation
· Q3: First customer shipments (limited release)
· Q4: Service network establishment

Key Milestones:

· Regulatory approval in key markets
· Production capacity of 100 units/month
· First 50 units deployed and operational
· Service level agreements with customers

7.4 Phase 4: Scale and Expansion (2029+)

2029: Market Expansion

· Production capacity expansion to 500 units/month
· Entry into home care market
· International expansion beyond initial markets
· Development of specialized application modules

2030+: Future Generations

· Quantum processor scaling to 1024+ qubits
· Integration with emerging technologies (brain-computer interface, etc.)
· New form factors and specialized variants
· Expansion into adjacent markets (education, hospitality, etc.)

7.5 Risk Mitigation

Technical Risks:

· Quantum hardware scaling: Parallel development of quantum-inspired classical algorithms
· 6G deployment delays: Fallback to 5G with reduced capabilities
· Sensor accuracy: Redundant sensing with voting algorithms
· Software complexity: Modular development with formal verification

Regulatory Risks:

· Medical device approval: Early and continuous engagement with regulators
· Liability frameworks: Insurance products and limitation of liability
· Data privacy: Built-in compliance with all major regulations
· International variations: Modular design for regional customization

Market Risks:

· Adoption resistance: Focus on demonstrable ROI and clinical evidence
· Competition: Continuous innovation and patent protection
· Economic downturn: Focus on cost-saving applications
· Technology disruption: Modular architecture for easy upgrades

