GLOSSARY

6G: Sixth generation wireless communication technology offering terahertz frequencies, ultra-low latency, and massive connectivity.

Quantum Advantage: When a quantum computer solves a problem faster or better than the best possible classical computer.

Embodied AI: Artificial intelligence that learns through interaction with the physical world via a body.

Haptic Telepresence: Remote operation with sense of touch feedback.

Series Elastic Actuator: Actuator with intentional elasticity for safe human-robot interaction.

Multi-Modal Sensing: Integration of data from different types of sensors (visual, thermal, audio, etc.).

Federated Learning: Machine learning approach where models are trained across decentralized devices without sharing data.

Post-Quantum Cryptography: Cryptographic algorithms secure against attacks by quantum computers.

HL7 FHIR: Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources, a standard for healthcare data exchange.

ISO 26262: International standard for functional safety of electrical and electronic systems.

